While building application on aihub.instabase.com (http://aihub.instabase.com), complex prompts are not completing the run. The  attached app URL complex prompt is running for an hour and giving no results.
https://aihub.uat.instabase.com/hub/build/9cdf6bcb-4fe1-45d5-8557-d6a93043e797
cc: @Shubham
@Saumya your URL points to UAT, but I did have the same issue on Production (aihub.instabase.com (http://aihub.instabase.com)) just now
Sounds like similar issue on both the environment.

<!subteam^S05BKH20B4K>, can you take a look at this?
cc: @avi, @Varun Jain

Let’s use aihub support channel for all issues. Created thread there — https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1697106662713869 (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1697106662713869)
Do we have a jira ticket for this? With the new focus on measuring issues I’m keen to make sure things like this are logged and measured.
Yes, we need to keep track of release related issues to keep ourselves accountable. I’ll create a Jira ticket for the issue.

Was finding this as well last night, if you reload the page it will correctly pull the result and save the field (if you already clicked "save field") - even if it's giving you the infinite load circle. Not a long term solution ofc
I closed the insights ticket and open an EPD ticket instead. Let's make sure field reported issues go to Jira EPD board or ZD -- this is where the metrics will be generated from
